description: An artist considers some possible national rebranding for the occasion of Canada's birthday.
title: Canada’s Edgy 150th Birthday Rebranding
title_page: Canada’s Edgy 150th Birthday Rebranding - The New York Times
text: Author and illustrator Graham Roumieu was raised in Smithers, British Columbia, where the egg carton was invented, which is a bad-ass way of storing eggs.
